Controversial crossdresser, Idris Okuneye, aka Bobrisky has thrown his weight behind a social media celebrity, Ismailia Mustapha aka Mompha. Mompha, the internet celebrity, has been facing trial over alleged N6b fraud. He was granted a bail of N200m on Tuesday in Lagos. Bobrisky took his Instagram to pledge his support and heap praise on Mompha who he described as a strong man. “Like have always say it and I will continue to say it, have known you to be a strong Mompha, not a weak man,” he posted. “I stand and re-stand with you. Everything will be over soon because I know you can handle this, it’s just a little distraction.”   Nigerian artistes with prominent parents     Why I abandoned school, by Portable     ‘Davido is selfless and a blessing to many’   - Advertisement - The 30-year-old transgender also shaded Mompha’s critics. “It hurt to see people hailing you on ur page are still the same people commenting trash on blog about you. Human beings are the first people we should run away from before anything…” The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission had arraigned Mompha and his firm, Ismalob Global Investment Limited for alleged money laundering to the tune of over an N6billion. On Tuesday, Justice Mojisola Dada of an Ikeja Special Offences Court granted him bail of N200 million with two sureties in the like sum.